    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "items": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Harm"
        },
        {
          "type": "span",
          "items": [
            {
              "type": "icon",
              "icon": "harm",
              "color": "black"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "is a type of token that is added to cards by tests and other effects. What it represents varies considerably from card to card. On"
        },
        {
          "type": "a",
          "items": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "beings"
            }
          ],
          "link": {
            "id": "rules_glossary/b/beings",
            "anchor": "",
            "url": "/docs/rules_glossary/B/being"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "it may represent physical harm, but it can also represent distress. On"
        },
        {
          "type": "a",
          "items": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "features"
            }
          ],
          "link": {
            "id": "rules_glossary/f/features",
            "anchor": "",
            "url": "/docs/rules_glossary/F/features"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "it may represent how much damage a physical object can suffer before it breaks, or the process of hacking a path through the brush. It can also be a measure of how much material can be harvested from a plant before nothing of use remains."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "items": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Your instinct may be to think of a card\u2019s"
        },
        {
          "type": "a",
          "items": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "harm threshold"
            }
          ],
          "link": {
            "id": "rules_glossary/h/harm_threshold",
            "anchor": "",
            "url": "/docs/rules_glossary/H/harm_threshold"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "as its \u201chit points,\u201d that is, the amount of damage it can sustain before it is killed or destroyed, but that it not necessarily the case. You clear a card with harm when the amount of harm equals or exceeds its"
        },
        {
          "type": "a",
          "items": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "harm threshold"
            }
          ],
          "link": {
            "id": "rules_glossary/h/harm_threshold",
            "anchor": "",
            "url": "/docs/rules_glossary/H/harm_threshold"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". This means you've simply done enough damage or caused enough distress to cause it to flee. When you clear a feature from harm, you\u2019ve overcome it through force or have depleted it of its resources."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
